# German Learning – Word Extraction

## Context

Project is for learning German at B1 level. User writes texts in `texts/`, AI extracts words and distributes them to `vocabulary/` by type.

## Text File Naming Format

New texts in `texts/` use format: **`Y-m-d_H:i_title.md`**

Example: `2025-03-10_14:30_mein-tag.md` (date_time_title)

## Text Content Format in texts/

When user says "create new text" and gives a title, create **empty file** with only:

```markdown
# [Title]

[Y-m-d]
```

No additional content – user writes the text themselves.

All `.md` files in `texts/` must follow this format (title + date).

## Word Type Mapping

| German type | File | Examples |
|-------------|------|----------|
| Substantiv | vocabulary/Substantive.md | die Arbeit, der Tag |
| Verb | vocabulary/Verben.md | gehen, lesen |
| Adjektiv | vocabulary/Adjektive.md | freundlich, wichtig |
| Adverb | vocabulary/Adverbien.md | sehr, oft |
| Präposition | vocabulary/Präpositionen.md | in, auf, mit |
| Konjunktion, Partikel, Pronomen | vocabulary/Andere.md | und, aber, ich |

**No subfolders** – one file per type.

## Vocabulary File Format

One file per type. Words grouped by source (text):

```markdown
# [Type]

## [text-name]

| Word | Article | Translation | Example |
|------|---------|--------------|---------|
| Arbeit | die | work | Ich gehe zur Arbeit. |
```

- **Substantive**: include gender (der/die/das)
- **Verben**: infinitive only. Verb tenses (Präteritum, Perfekt, etc.) are extracted separately – not in the vocabulary.
- **Translation**: always in Serbian
- Do not duplicate words – check existing files before adding

## B1 Level

B1 covers ~2500–3000 words: everyday life, work, health, travel, education. Skip A1/A2 basic words (ich, und, ist) unless contextually important.
